President Obama dropped by a meeting between National Security Advisor Tom Donilon and President-elect of Peru Ollanta Humala in the Roosevelt Room. They discussed the importance of the US and Peru's relationship in addressing bilateral, regional, and global issues. They also talked about the need for sound market-based economic policies coupled with efforts to increase economic and social inclusion. President Obama expressed the US' commitment to supporting similar efforts in Peru. They also discussed deepening environmental cooperation and enhancing counternarcotics cooperation and citizen security. President-elect Humala was accompanied by his wife, Peruvian Ambassador Luis Chuquihuara, and Peruvian Congressman Daniel Abugattas.